Biko

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Rice Base
	•	1 1/2 cups (300 g) glutinous rice, rinsed well

Cooking Liquid
	•	1.7 cups (400 ml) full-fat coconut milk
	•	0.85 cup (200 ml) water

Sweetening
	•	1 cup (200 g) brown sugar
	•	1/2 teaspoon salt

Latik (Coconut Topping)
	•	0.85 cup (200 ml) coconut cream

⸻

Method
	1.	Rinse Rice
Rinse glutinous rice under cold water until runoff is clear. Drain well.
	2.	Cook Rice
Combine rice, coconut milk, and water in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat.
	3.	Thicken
Cook, stirring frequently, about 25 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender and glossy.
	4.	Sweeten
Add brown sugar and salt. Continue cooking and stirring 8–10 minutes until fully dissolved and mixture darkens slightly with a caramel aroma.
	5.	Rest
Transfer to a serving dish. Smooth the surface and rest 10 minutes.
	6.	Make Latik
Simmer coconut cream in a small saucepan, stirring, until oil separates and solids turn golden brown. Remove immediately.
	7.	Finish
Spoon latik evenly over warm biko. Serve warm.

⸻

Optional Enhancements
	•	Substitute coconut sugar for brown sugar (deeper, more traditional flavor)
	•	Add a pandan leaf to the rice while cooking (remove before sweetening)
	•	Lightly salt the latik for sharper contrast
	•	Serve with ripe mango or banana for balance